  {

   "id": "7f88039c-eaef-495e-924f-8ac1f3146123",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#4. 'Size' column has sizes in Kb as well as Mb. To analyze, we need to convert these to numeric.\n",
    "\n",
    "#4.11 -- Extract the numeric value from the column \n",
    "def convert_to_numeric(x):\n",
    "    if type(x) == int or type(x) == float:\n",
    "        return x\n",
    "    if 'k' in x:\n",
    "        if len(x) > 1:\n",
    "            return float(x.replace('k', ''))\n",
    "        return 1.0\n",
    "\n",
    "    # 4.12 Multiply the value by 1,000, if size is mentioned in Mb \n",
    "    if 'M' in x:\n",
    "        if len(x) > 1:\n",
    "            return float(x.replace('M', '')) * 1000\n",
    "        return 1000.0\n",
    "    if 'e' in x:\n",
    "        return 0.0\n",
    "\n",
    "df['Size'] = df['Size'].apply(convert_to_numeric)"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "#4.2 Reviews is a numeric field that is loaded as a string field. Convert it to numeric (int/float).\n",
    "df['Reviews'] = df['Reviews'].astype(int)\n",
    "df['Last Updated'] = df['Last Updated'].astype('datetime64[ns]')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 586,
   "id": "0f8daaf3-9685-443e-a72f-ac855e56eaf9",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#4.3 Installs field is currently stored as string and has values like 1,000,000+.\n",
    "#4.31 -- Treat 1,000,000+ as 1,000,000\n",
    "#4.32 -- Remove ‘+’, ‘,’ from the field, convert it to integer\n",
    "df['Installs'] = df['Installs'].str.replace('+', '', regex=False)\n",
    "df['Installs'] = df['Installs'].str.replace(',', '', regex=False)\n",
    "df['Installs'] = pd.to_numeric(df['Installs'], errors='coerce')\n",
    "df['Installs'] = df['Installs'].fillna(0)\n",
    "df['Installs'] = df['Installs'].astype(int)"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "#6.1 Handling Price outliers (>= $200).\n",
    "# - Having an app that costs over $200 is very sus and could be a scam.\n",
    "def outliers (df,col):\n",
    "    Q1 = df[col].quantile(0.25)\n",
    "    Q3 = df[col].quantile(0.75)\n",
    "    IQR = Q3 - Q1\n",
    "    df = df.loc[~((df[col] < (Q1 - 1.5)) | (df[col] > (Q3 + 1.5 * IQR))),]\n",
    "    return df\n",
    "\n",
    "df = df.loc[df[\"Price\"] < 200 ,]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",

   "id": "9708ad22-5783-4ddb-b494-a04302701b55",

   "source": [

    "# - These are all star apps that don’t help with the analysis and, in fact, will skew it. \n",
    "# - Drop records having more than 2 million reviews.\n",
    "df = outliers(df,\"Reviews\")"
   ]

   "source": [
    "# Storing the Category column into 'x' varible that will and delete Category column from inp2.\n",
    "# + Concatinate the encoded columns to inp2 df.\n",
    "def create_dummies(df, col):\n",
    "    df[col] = pd.Categorical(df[col])\n",
    "\n",
    "    x = df[[col]]\n",
    "    del df[col]\n",
    "\n",
    "    dummies = pd.get_dummies(x,prefix=col)\n",
    "    df = pd.concat([df,dummies], axis = 1)\n",
    "    return df\n",
    "\n",
    "inp2 = create_dummies(inp2, 'Category')"
   ]
  },
